                <h2>Letter A</h2>
                <p>The letter 'A' in ASL is not only the beginning of the alphabet but also a key building block in many
                    signs. Mastering this sign is an important step in your ASL learning journey. Let's dive into how to
                    form the 'A' sign correctly.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Start with Your Hand Open:</strong> Begin with your hand open, palm facing the person
                        you are communicating with. This starting position is crucial for clarity.</li>
                    <li><strong>Curl Your Fingers:</strong> Gently curl all of your fingers into your palm, making a
                        fist. Make sure your fingers are comfortably folded.</li>
                    <li><strong>Position Your Thumb:</strong> Now, focus on your thumb, which is the key to this sign.
                        Instead of tucking it inside, extend your thumb up and rest it along the side of your fist. It
                        should be pointing upwards, making your hand look like a tight, little 'A'.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>And there you have it! You've successfully formed the ASL sign for the letter 'A'. Practice this sign
                    a few times to get comfortable with it. Remember, the position of your thumb is what differentiates
                    this sign from others. Happy signing!</p>
